Ode xxvm.

The poet bids Lyde join him in celebrating the Neptunalia, July 2 3rd. Kiaesling suggests that Horace, strolling along the street, finds himself before Lyde’s house, and that the notion of keeping the Neptunalia with her occurs to him as a happy thought. The scene would thus be in Lyde’s house, or rather in her garden, for the Neptunalia were celebrated in arbours made of boughs. Lyde is doubtloes the shy singer of 11. 11. 21.
